narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Really depends on your preference for language. If you like grammar, take German!
Decent work load, good course for a beginning language
I would recommend this course. Initially I was not excited to take this class, but it ended up being one of my most challenging and fun classes.
German is a great program at Yale and I would highly recommend a future language student to take German.

A swiftly moving course with reasonable classwork and homework. Useful information is imparted and the emphasis is on speaking. I would recommend the class since it was accommodating and relaxed enough so that most would feel comfortable in it.
